## SQL(Structured Query Language)

## What is SQL?
->Structured Query Language (SQL) was developed by IBM in the 1970s, 
->It was one of the first commercial databases available for corporate companies. 

->These types of databases adopt the structured and relational model in data management.


## Types of SQL statements
1. Data Definition Language (DDL) 
-->Used to manipulate schema objects
-->Permits and revokes database privileges 
-->Includes commands such as CREATE, ALTER, DROP etc. 


2.Data Manipulation Language (DML)
-->Used to read and manipulate data stored in
schema objects 
-->Includes commands such as SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE etc.